v class="amazingcarousel-hover-effect" style="display:none;position:absolute;left:0;top:0;width:100%;height:100%;cursor:pointer;background-image:url('https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/slider/skins/hoveroverlay-64-64-6.png');background-repeat:no-repeat;background-position:center center;"></div></div><div class="amazingcarousel-title"></div></div></li><li class="amazingcarousel-item" style="display: block; position: relative; background-image: none; background-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; float: left; width: 150px;"><div class="amazingcarousel-item-container" style="position: relative; margin: 0px 2px;"><div class="amazingcarousel-image"> <a href="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_5943.jpg" title="" class="html5lightbox" data-group="amazingcarousel"> <img src="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_5943.jpg" alt="" style="left: -80px;"> </a><div class="amazingcarousel-hover-effect" style="display:none;position:absolute;left:0;top:0;width:100%;height:100%;cursor:pointer;background-image:url('https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/slider/skins/hoveroverlay-64-64-6.png');background-repeat:no-repeat;background-position:center center;"></div></div><div class="amazingcarousel-title"></div></div></li><li class="amazingcarousel-item" style="display: block; position: relative; background-image: none; background-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; float: left; width: 150px;"><div class="amazingcarousel-item-container" style="position: relative; margin: 0px 2px;"><div class="amazingcarousel-image"> <a href="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_5991.jpg" title="" class="html5lightbox" data-group="amazingcarousel"> <img src="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_5991.jpg" alt=""> </a><div class="amazingcarousel-hover-effect" style="display:none;position:absolute;left:0;top:0;width:100%;height:100%;cursor:pointer;background-image:url('https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/slider/skins/hoveroverlay-64-64-6.png');background-repeat:no-repeat;background-position:center center;"></div></div><div class="amazingcarousel-title"></div></div></li><li class="amazingcarousel-item" style="display: block; position: relative; background-image: none; background-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; float: left; width: 150px;"><div class="amazingcarousel-item-container" style="position: relative; margin: 0px 2px;"><div class="amazingcarousel-image"> <a href="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_6027.jpg" title="" class="html5lightbox" data-group="amazingcarousel"> <img src="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_6027.jpg" alt=""> </a><div class="amazingcarousel-hover-effect" style="display:none;position:absolute;left:0;top:0;width:100%;height:100%;cursor:pointer;background-image:url('https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/slider/skins/hoveroverlay-64-64-6.png');background-repeat:no-repeat;background-position:center center;"></div></div><div class="amazingcarousel-title"></div></div></li><li class="amazingcarousel-item" style="display: block; position: relative; background-image: none; background-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; float: left; width: 150px;"><div class="amazingcarousel-item-container" style="position: relative; margin: 0px 2px;"><div class="amazingcarousel-image"> <a href="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_6045.jpg" title="" class="html5lightbox" data-group="amazingcarousel"> <img src="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_6045.jpg" alt=""> </a><div class="amazingcarousel-hover-effect" style="display:none;position:absolute;left:0;top:0;width:100%;height:100%;cursor:pointer;background-image:url('https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/slider/skins/hoveroverlay-64-64-6.png');background-repeat:no-repeat;background-position:center center;"></div></div><div class="amazingcarousel-title"></div></div></li><div style="clear:both;"></div></ul></div></div><div class="amazingcarousel-prev" style="overflow: hidden; position: absolute; cursor: pointer; width: 32px; height: 32px; background: url(&quot;https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/slider/skins/arrows-32-32-1.png&quot;) left top no-repeat; display: block;"></div><div class="amazingcarousel-next" style="overflow: hidden; position: absolute; cursor: pointer; width: 32px; height: 32px; background: url(&quot;https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/slider/skins/arrows-32-32-1.png&quot;) right top no-repeat; display: block;"></div></div></div></div></div><p><strong>The popularity of this model among brides is because it reflects almost all following fashion trends:</strong></p><ul><li>a delicate elastic top with embroidery;</li><li>a built-in bra or cut-off cups;</li><li>a tender silhouette of a lace dress;</li><li>an open back and a short lacing on air loops;</li><li>and a full detachable skirt with a train.</li></ul><p><strong>This course contains a lot of couture techniques. I will show you the following:</strong></p><ul><li>how to seamlessly cover the corset with lace;</li><li>how to join a lace folded skirt to a dress, so that you don’t have any extra thickness and the transition from a corset to a dress is smooth and invisible;</li><li>how to sew an elastic top between a face and a lining;</li><li>how to make a lining with built-in cups.</li></ul><p><strong>The special feature of the course is tambour (luneville) sequin embroidery.</strong></p><p>The process of cutting, sewing and decoration of a garment from scratch to final operations is described and illustrated in detail.<br> All necessary patterns and bonuses (for printing) are attached as follows:</p><ul><li>2 tables for AUTOMATIC pattern adjustments calculation for all patterns of this course;</li><li>patterns of a corset face and a corset lining;</li><li>patterns of decorative details.</li></ul><div><p><strong>The aim of the course</strong>&nbsp;is my great desire to teach the techniques of making such dresses. All the techniques can be used in various combinations, so that you can sew different models of evening, cocktail, prom and wedding dresses.</p><p><strong>The course is useful</strong>&nbsp;both to beginners as well as to experienced professionals in making wedding and evening dresses. It can be handy for dressmaking atelier personnel as a professional development training.</p></div><div></div><div><p><strong>Author:</strong>&nbsp;Tatiana Kozorovitsky</p><p><strong>Total length:</strong>&nbsp;5h 00m</p></div></div></div><div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane" id="transcript"><div class="overlay"></div><div itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/Article"> <span itemprop="publisher" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/Organization"><meta itemprop="name" content="Corset Academy"> <span itemprop="logo" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/ImageObject"><meta itemprop="name" content="Corset Academy logo"><meta itemprop="text" content="Corset Academy logo"><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset/img/logo.png"><meta itemprop="contentUrl" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset/img/logo.png"><meta itemprop="width" content="303"><meta itemprop="height" content="49"><meta itemprop="encodingFormat" content="image/png"> </span><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/"><meta itemprop="sameAs" content="https://www.facebook.com/corsetacademy"> </span> <span itemprop="author" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/Person"><meta itemprop="name" content="Tatiana Kozorovitsky"> <span itemprop="image" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/ImageObject"><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/uploads/MVI_3285.MOV.00_00_31_09.Still001-128x128.jpg"><meta itemprop="contentUrl" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/uploads/MVI_3285.MOV.00_00_31_09.Still001-128x128.jpg"><meta itemprop="width" content="128"><meta itemprop="height" content="128"><meta itemprop="encodingFormat" content="image/jpeg"> </span><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/author/infocorsetacademy-net/"><meta itemprop="sameAs" content="http://www.corsetacademy.net"> </span><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/tutorial-42-drafting-of-padding-pattern-for-the-skirt/"><meta itemprop="mainEntityOfPage" content="https://corsetacademy.net/tutorial-42-drafting-of-padding-pattern-for-the-skirt/"><meta itemprop="datePublished" content="2018-12-05T21:19:21+00:00"><meta itemprop="dateModified" content="2018-12-05T21:19:21+00:00"><meta itemprop="copyrightYear" content="2018"><meta itemprop="inLanguage" content="en_US"><meta itemprop="name" content="Tutorial 42. Drafting of padding pattern for the skirt."><meta itemprop="headline" content="Tutorial 42. Drafting of padding pattern for the skirt."><meta itemprop="description" content="At this tutorial I will demonstrate how to draft pattern of the skirt padding using the construction we have made on the dress-form."><meta itemprop="articleSection" content="Wedding Dress with Detachable Full Skirt. Part 2."><meta itemprop="keywords" content="wedding dress with detachable full skirt. part 2., video"> <span itemprop="image" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/ImageObject"><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset/img/logo.png"><meta itemprop="contentUrl" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset/img/logo.png"><meta itemprop="width" content="303"><meta itemprop="height" content="49"><meta itemprop="encodingFormat" content="image/png"> </span><div itemprop="articleBody"><h1>Tutorial 42. Drafting of padding pattern for the skirt.</h1><p><strong>At this tutorial I will demonstrate how to draft pattern of the skirt padding using the construction we have made on the dress-form. </strong></p><p><strong>Certainly, the pattern is made using a mock-up method. </strong>There are no any other options!</p><p><strong>I pinned the final patterns to the board. </strong>My pattern consists of 6 pieces or 6 mock-up patches.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2042.files/image002.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>You may have a question: </strong>why do we have 6 pattern pieces, when we used 4 vertical straps dividing the model into 3 pieces? The thing is that I had to cut each of three pieces as during еру construction of round shapes of padding we need to make darts.</p><p><strong>At the same time, the pattern is traced to mock-up fabric between straps and only after I make corrections. </strong>It is easy and clear to work that way.</p><p><strong>So, I draft a pattern of the first gore of my construction. </strong></p><p><strong>I place a mock-up fabric parallel to the first front strap and fix it along straps with pins. </strong></p><p><strong>Please pay attention </strong>that in order to avoid displacement during drafting I additionally fixed all plastic circles with one additional office pin. If one pin falls, the second pin will keep the shape of construction. I strongly recommend using additional pins to ensure the previous work is not screwed up.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2042.files/image004.jpg" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2042.files/image006.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>I neatly cover the area with the mock-up fabric and see that one place requires dart, </strong>otherwise the shape will be flat. I make a necessary dart and pin it and the mock-up fabric together.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2042.files/image008.jpg" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2042.files/image010.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>I take a disappearing ink pen and trace dart and gore along the edge of front strap, the edge of lower circle, the middle of the next strap and waist.</strong></p><p><strong>Important note: I strongly recommend tracing pattern with the disappearing ink pen as </strong>it draws when you hardly touch the mock-up fabric and there is no risk to displace model. If you are very careful the pattern is traced with 100% accuracy!</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2042.files/image012.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>Then I draft pattern pieces between all straps. </strong></p><p><strong><br> <img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2042.files/image014.jpg" alt=""></strong></p><p><strong>So, I traced all three pattern pieces and every pattern piece has a dart. </strong></p><p><strong>I cut the pieces on the mock-up fabric and join pieces with hand basting stitches and simultaneously I fold darts.</strong></p><p><strong>I get the dome-shaped mock-up, which I put on the construction on the dress-form with seam allowances facing up. </strong>I make alterations if needed. If you traced pieces thoroughly, there would be no alteration required.</p><p><strong>After corrections I draw new curve lines along the tops of darts without taking the mock-up off the dress-form. </strong>You need to do it through tops of darts regardless of the number of darts. This is done to have a flat pattern when we put it on the table. So, you will have a real pattern!</p><p><strong>Why do I recommend doing it this way?</strong> Usually, such forms like our padding are made of thick fabric, so it is not practical to make darts! It is better to make more vertical strap than darts! That is why I made vertical curve lines through tops of darts and bisected each pattern piece in my mind.</p><p><strong>I undo the first mock-up, cut every piece along curve lines, </strong>made along tops of darts and make a new mock-up. I carefully check the conformity of lengths of all curve lines.&nbsp;&nbsp; <strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><p><strong>At this stage it is important to sign all pieces (numbers in black)&nbsp; and the most important is to number curve lines with the same numbers, which will be joined together (numbers in red). </strong>Otherwise you can mix up and trust me, you will need to redo everything!</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2042.files/image016.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>Again I baste the mock-up of the padding, put it over construction on the dress-form and check it.</strong></p><p><strong>Then I trace plastic boning of the construction on this mock-up.</strong></p><p><strong>I undo model into 6 pieces.</strong> Now I need to add seam allowances as we have already basted, checked mock-up and measured precisely the lengths of joining sides. The marked bones transit from one piece into other and the crossing point of bones and curve lines will be the reference points for joining of those pieces.</p><p><strong>Thus, you have the final pattern of the skirt padding. You just need to add seam allowances and start sewing! </strong></p><p><strong>Although, in order to keep a shape of our padding we need to make it harder with internal gore. </strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2042.files/image018.jpg" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2042.files/image020.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>Besides, we need to make a small belt, with which our detail will be attached to the skirt.</strong></p><p><strong><br> <img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2042.files/image022.jpg" alt=""></strong></p><p><strong>It is very easy to draft a pattern of internal gore. The action plan is as follows.</strong></p><p><strong>I disassemble the construction on the dress-form. Before it I need to pin along the outmost straps and the lower circle. </strong>Besides, I recommend taking a photo of construction, so that you will an opportunity to restore it by photo if something goes wrong.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2042.files/image024.jpg" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2042.files/image026.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>I place a mock-up fabric. I make an incision, which will be joined with side seam, </strong>for easier placing of the fabric on the dress-form at the distortion area along the side. I attach fabric to the dress-form outside of the area marked with pins.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2042.files/image028.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong><br> <img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2042.files/image030.jpg" alt=""></strong></p><p><strong>Then I draw the side seam, the waistline and the perimeter lines of gore along pins (front, back and lower edge) with the disappearing ink pen.</strong></p><p><strong><br> <img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2042.files/image032.jpg" alt=""></strong></p><p><strong><br> <img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2042.files/image034.jpg" alt=""></strong></p><p><strong>That is all, the pattern of gore is ready! </strong>I do not recommend cutting this piece immediately, it is better to sew padding, check the conformity of lengths of padding and gore and only after you can cut, sew and join gore with padding.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2042.files/image036.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>I put the ready padding for skirt on the dress-form. </strong>Please note I made the absolute copy of the mock-up shape. The padding matches the position of straps and circles of my construction, which are marked with pins on the dress-form.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2042.files/image038.jpg" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2042.files/image040.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>The construction is rather solid and can hold the weight of tulle skirt and even a layer of atlas! &nbsp;</strong></p><p><strong>Which materials can be used for such skirt paddings? </strong></p><p><strong>In principle any fabric will do except for stretching fabric, </strong>for instance, jersey.</p><p>It depends on purpose of padding.</p><p><strong>In my garment I purposely made the visible padding under the layers of tulle.</strong></p><p><strong>I wanted </strong>that you could see in the advertisement to the course that there is such padding under skirt and everybody, who is interested in making such padding, could get to know that I teach about making paddings in this particular course.</p><p><strong>So, I made this padding from transparent fabric.</strong></p><p><strong>If desired, </strong>I could hide padding under the opaque skirt, but then the internal skirt design would not be quite clear.</p><p><strong>My padding is made of synthetic mesh fabric </strong>similar to one we call a corset mesh fabric for transparent corsets , but this mesh is thinner, softer and tender with finer cells.</p><p>In our stores this fabric is called mesh fabric for skirts.</p><p>At present the modern skirts with various folds and rather heavy elements is strengthened by using such mesh fabric.</p><p><strong>Paddings under skirts can be made of atlas, padanje, taffeta and organza or that is from any fabric.</strong></p><p><strong>Every time </strong>and for each particular case everything will depend on weight of skirt, which padding needs to hold.</p><p><strong>If your skirt is light and weightless, </strong>like in my case, then it is enough to make a light and weightless padding.</p><p><strong>If you need to hold a heavy jacquard skirt, </strong>then you need to make the heavier padding and use harder plastic boning, for instance, you need to use 7mm plastic bones instead of 2 mm bones or to replace the Rigeline bones used for my padding to plastic or steel spiral bones.</p><p><strong>Thus, it depends on weight, which padding should hold.</strong></p><p><strong>The pattern of this padding is certainly attached to the course.</strong></p><p>Although, if you want to create something of your own, which may be even more original and intricate, then the technique is already known to you!</p></div></div></div><div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane" id="pattern"><p>Sewing patterns are in PDF format. To print sewing patterns open the files, press “print” and choose&nbsp;<strong>“print in actual size”</strong>. In each&nbsp;file the pattern is divided &nbsp;to A4 paper sheets for home printers.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h4><strong>Automatic Pattern Alterations Calculator:</strong></h4><h4><strong><a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/calculations/ENGcorset/corset.htm" target="_blank">The Dress (Corset)</a></strong></h4><h4><strong><a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/calculations/ENGskirt/ENGskirt.htm" target="_blank">The Skirt</a></strong></h4><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p> <a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/patterns/belt%2C%20bow.pdf" target="_blank" class=""><img src="https://cdn.shortpixel.ai/client/q_glossy,ret_img/https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/pdf.png"> The Belf and The Bow</a><br><a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/patterns/corset%20-%20front.pdf" target="_blank" class=""><img src="https://cdn.shortpixel.ai/client/q_glossy,ret_img/https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/pdf.png"> Corset Front</a><br><a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/patterns/corset%20-%20lining.pdf" target="_blank" class=""><img src="https://cdn.shortpixel.ai/client/q_glossy,ret_img/https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/pdf.png"> Corset Lining</a><br><a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/patterns/pattern.pdf" target="_blank" class=""><img src="https://cdn.shortpixel.ai/client/q_glossy,ret_img/https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/pdf.png"> The Pattern</a><br><a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/patterns/skirt.pdf" target="_blank" class=""><img src="https://cdn.shortpixel.ai/client/q_glossy,ret_img/https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/pdf.png"> The Skirt</a><br><a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/patterns/top.pdf" target="_blank" class=""><img src="https://cdn.shortpixel.ai/client/q_glossy,ret_img/https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/pdf.png"> The Top</a><br></div><div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane" id="diploma"><div class="dark-get-started margin-0"><p>In order to receive the Corset Academy graduation diploma you need to submit your graduation work.<br> Upload the photo of the garment that you made after completing the course.<br> I will personally review your work.<br> After the approval you will receive a personalized diploma to your email box, no longer than within 1 business day.</p><p class="text-right">Tatiana Kozorovitsky.</p><form id="diplomaForm"><h4>Your datails:</h4><div class="form-group"> <input type="text" id="firstname" class="form-control" placeholder="Enter first name" required=""><p class="firstname error">Enter your first name</p></div><div class="form-group"> <input type="text" id="lastname" class="form-control" placeholder="Enter last name" required=""><p class="lastname error">Enter your last name</p></div><h4>Choose a course:</h4><div class="radio"> <input type="radio" name="course" id="option1" value="1"> <label for="option1"> <em>Wedding gowns design and sewing course.</em> </label></div><div class="radio"> <input type="radio" name="course" id="option2" value="2"> <label for="option2"> <em>Evening dresses design and sewing course.</em> </label></div><div class="radio"> <input type="radio" name="course" id="option3" value="3"> <label for="option3"> <em>Corsetry design and sewing course.</em> </label></div><p class="course error margin-10-bottom">Select course</p><div class="form-group"> <label class="uploadbutton"><div class="button">Choose file</div><div class="pull-left"><div class="input">No file selected</div></div> <input type="file" id="fileupload" name="files[]" data-url="https://corsetacademy.net/diploma/upload/"> </label><div id="progress" class="progress" style="display: none;"><div class="bar progress-bar progress-bar-warning progress-bar-striped active" role="progressbar" style="width: 0%;"></div></div> <input type="hidden" id="uploadDataUrl"><p class="upload error">Please upload photo of your work.</p><p>Max file size 2 Mb</p></div> <input type="hidden" id="userEmail" value="ngochuy.mmt@gmail.com"> <button id="submitDiploma" type="submit" class="btn btn-green-simple">Submit</button><h3 id="submitSpinner" class="text-center" style="display:none"><i class="fa fa-spinner fa-spin"></i></h3></form><h4 id="statusAnswer" class="text-center"></h4><div class="clearfix"></div><h3 class="get-pro text-center">The example of the diploma:</h3> <a href="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/diploma_example.png" class="wplightbox" title="Diploma Example"><div id="diploma_example"></div> </a></div></div><div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane" id="faq"><p class="text-center"><i class="fa fa-spinner fa-pulse fa-3x"></i></p></div></div></div></div>

